Thence, under protection of the great woods, keeping successively the mountains, which separate Oork from Kerry and Limemck, they fought their way to the fastnesses of Aharlow, near the town of Tipperary. Entrusting here to some noble friend, the second son of Donald, a child two years of age, they effected their retreat north through the barony of Kilmanagh, over the Sliebh Feflim mountaius, on by the Ormondes, to the banks of the Shannon, above Lough Derg.
